Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Peel and cut @Carrots{4} diagonally into ½-inch-thick pieces. Thinly slice @Chives{1/4%ounce}. Place potatoes in a large #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Boil until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Drain and return to pot.

While potatoes cook, toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{4%tsp}, @salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Roast until tender and lightly browned at the edges, about ~{15%minutes}. Drizzle with @Honey{1%tbsp} and return to oven until caramelized and golden brown, ~{5-7%minutes} more.

While carrots roast, pat @Sirloin Steak{14%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until browned and cooked to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for ~{5%minutes}. Wipe out pan.

Add @Beef Demi-Glace{1} and ¼ cup water to same pan. Stir over low heat until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tbsp} and any resting juices from steak. Stir until butter has melted. Turn off heat; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Mash potatoes with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth. Reserve 1 TBSP chives; stir rest into mashed potatoes with @Sour Cream{4%tbsp} and @Butter{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice steak. Divide carrots, potatoes, and steak between #plates{}. Spoon sauce over potatoes and steak. Sprinkle carrots with @Chili Flakes{1%tsp}(to taste). Garnish the plate with reserved chives.